{"tid":1280153,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"[推到攬炒見到] re: UK expat HKPF commandants","createTime":"2019-07-03T01:14:18.000Z","updateTime":"2019-07-14T16:22:28.000Z","uid":61499,"like":23,"dislike":2,"uniUserReply":15,"replies":[{"pid":"39d579b18f5816ab8ea644e4e8409f5accb14ae2","tid":1280153,"uid":61499,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-07-03T01:14:18.000Z","msg":"本來都廢時用petition方法去搞, 但見Helen Goodman MP講起無理由唔食住上<br />\n<br />\n本身呢單野都係上曬枱所以我無去搵新聞link etc for evidence<br />\n<br />\n貼上黎比攬炒team睇下覺得有冇用<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\nTitle: Hold British Ex-Pat Hong Kong Police officers accountable for their conspiracies to crimes against civil rights and unlawful use of force against Hong Kong protestors<br />\n<br />\nWe the undersigned are calling for the British government to hold British expats who serve in the Hong Kong Police Force accountable for their roles in conspiracies to police brutality, deemed unlawful by Amnesty International, against protestors and journalists alike.<br />\nThe officers who have been alleged to be the ones responsible for the use of crowd-control weapons and subsequently excessive force are Superintendent Justin Shave, Regional Commander Rupert Timothy Alan Dover and Commandant David Jordon. <br />\n<br />\nWe also draw the Parliament&rsquo;s attention to well publicized allegations of collusion between HKPF and Hong Kong Hospital Authority and their conspiracies to detain injured citizens of Hong Kong who may have been involved in the protests. <br />\nFinally, we request the Foreign Affairs Committee look into evidence that the storming of Legislative Council chamber on 1/7/19 has been deliberately allowed to happen by HKPF to vilify the campaign against Anti-Extradition Law Amendment Bill.<br />\n(petition page有冇得貼link講1/7)?"},{"pid":"f7dc4abb7d5f42b7749fe2bc2f4c772dc9e71fd7","tid":1280153,"uid":215876,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-07-03T01:16:25.000Z","msg":"推"},{"pid":"fca11b04b6